f=Executive Office/vista/marketplace/north-star-metric/references/nsm-playbook.md · h1:NSM Playbook: Tests, Archetypes, Metric Tree, Guardrails, Workflow=Read you need full operating detail NSM work five quality tests, Amplitude archetypes real examples, metric-tree structure input math, leading indicators, anti-metrics counter-metrics, step-by-step workflow, `metric_tree_builder.py` reference, troubleshooting, success criteria. · wh:makes good North Star Metric=defensible NSM passes five tests: · wh:makes good North Star Metric=\| Test \| Question \| If it fails... \| · wh:makes good North Star Metric=\|------\|----------\|---------------\| · wh:makes good North Star Metric=\| **Customer value** \| Does this number going up mean a customer got more value? \| Pick a different metric (e.g., move from "MAUs" to "weekly active accounts that completed a task") \| · wh:makes good North Star Metric=\| **Strategic alignment** \| Does it match how the company makes money? \| Pick a metric closer to monetization (e.g., "paid weekly active" not "weekly active") \| · wh:makes good North Star Metric=\| **Leading, not lagging** \| Does it predict long-term success, not just measure last quarter? \| Move upstream: revenue lags; activation leads \| · wh:makes good North Star Metric=\| **Single number** \| Can it be a single number on a dashboard? \| Compress: "DAU/MAU ratio" is one number; "DAU and MAU separately" is two \| · wh:makes good North Star Metric=\| **Movable** \| Can the team affect it within a quarter? \| Decompose into input metrics the team can move \| · h3:NSM archetypes (Amplitude framework)=\| Archetype \| What value is \| NSM example \| Used by (kind of company) \| · h3:NSM archetypes (Amplitude framework)=\|-----------\|---------------\|-------------\|---------------------------\| · h3:NSM archetypes (Amplitude framework)=\| **Attention** \| Time spent or engagement depth \| Time spent reading, video minutes watched \| Media, social networks \| · h3:NSM archetypes (Amplitude framework)=\| **Transaction** \| Purchases or trades \| Gross merchandise volume, rides booked \| Marketplaces, e-commerce \| · h3:NSM archetypes (Amplitude framework)=\| **Productivity** \| Tasks completed \| Weekly active teams creating >=1 deliverable \| SaaS productivity tools \| · h3:NSM archetypes (Amplitude framework)=\| **Communication** \| Messages or interactions \| Messages sent per WAU \| Messaging, social \| · h3:NSM archetypes (Amplitude framework)=\| **Subscriber** \| Recurring revenue retention \| Paid weekly active subscribers \| Subscription products \| · h3:NSM archetypes (Amplitude framework)=Pick archetype matches your business model. Mixing archetypes (e.g., chasing "messages sent" "subscribers") produces incoherent priorities. · h3:NSM examples (real companies)=\| Company \| NSM (publicly discussed) \| · h3:NSM examples (real companies)=\|---------\|--------------------------\| · h3:NSM examples (real companies)=\| Airbnb \| Nights booked \| · h3:NSM examples (real companies)=\| Spotify \| Time spent listening \| · h3:NSM examples (real companies)=\| Slack \| Active accounts sending >=2000 messages \| · h3:NSM examples (real companies)=\| Facebook (historically) \| Daily active users with 7 friends in 10 days \| · h3:NSM examples (real companies)=\| Quora \| Number of questions answered \| · h3:NSM examples (real companies)=NSM directly represents value customer getting what company doing. · h2:The metric tree=NSM alone actionable. decompose **input metrics** team directly move. metric tree formalizes decomposition. · h3:Structure=`North Star Metric \· \| \· ---------------------------------------- \· \|             \|             \|          \| \· Input #1     Input #2     Input #3    Input #4` · h3:Structure=**NSM top** single number, **Input metrics (3-5)** levers team pull. multiply sum NSM, **Leading indicators (2-3 input)** earliest measurable signals input moving · h3:Input metrics: math matters=Input metrics explicit mathematical relationship NSM. common patterns: · h3:Input metrics: math matters=\| Pattern \| Example \| · h3:Input metrics: math matters=\|---------\|---------\| · h3:Input metrics: math matters=\| **Multiplicative** \| Active users x Sessions per user x Actions per session = Total actions (NSM) \| · h3:Input metrics: math matters=\| **Additive** \| Web signups + Mobile signups + API signups = Total signups (NSM) \| · h3:Input metrics: math matters=\| **Funnel** \| Visitors -> Signups -> Activated -> Retained (each step is an input that gates the next) \| · h3:Input metrics: math matters=\| **Ratio** \| Engaged users / Total users = Engagement rate (NSM); inputs are engagement events and user counts \| · h3:Input metrics: math matters=Write formula explicitly: `NSM Input_1 Input_2 Input_3`. you cannot write formula, inputs really inputs they loosely related metrics. · h3:Leading indicators=leading indicator metric moves **before** input metric does. gives team early-warning signal. · h3:Leading indicators=\| Input metric \| Lagging signal \| Leading indicator \| · h3:Leading indicators=\|--------------\|----------------\|-------------------\| · h3:Leading indicators=\| Weekly retention \| Measured at day 7 \| Day-1 retention; first-day session count \| · h3:Leading indicators=\| New paid users \| Conversion at day 30 of trial \| Day-3 activation; trial usage depth \| · h3:Leading indicators=\| Support ticket resolution \| Average days to close \| First-response time; auto-deflect rate \| · h3:Leading indicators=\| Revenue per account \| Quarterly billing \| Expansion features adopted; seats added \| · h3:Leading indicators=Leading indicators team's daily/weekly dashboard. Inputs monthly review. NSM quarterly headline. · h2:Anti-metrics and counter-metrics=NSM powerful lever which means gamed. Two guardrails prevent this. · h3:Anti-metrics=**anti-metric** number move (or move specific bounded direction) while NSM moves up. They protect customer outcomes NSM inadvertently degrade. Examples: · h3:Anti-metrics=**NSM: video minutes watched** Anti-metrics: complaint rate, time-to-skip, churn within days first watch, **NSM: messages sent WAU** Anti-metrics: messages reported spam, abuse reports, blocked users, **NSM: nights booked** Anti-metrics: cancellation rate, host complaints, "would book again" rate · h3:Anti-metrics=Set explicit thresholds. "Churn exceed 4%" enforceable; "churn stay low" not. · h3:Counter-metrics=**counter-metric** metric team owns ensuring degrade because NSM chasing wrong thing. anti-metrics protect customer, counter-metrics protect business. Examples: · h3:Counter-metrics=**NSM: signups** Counter-metric: paid conversion rate (signups useless they convert), **NSM: time site** Counter-metric: revenue visit (time spent without purchase loss), **NSM: messages sent** Counter-metric: server costs message (engagement infinite cost bankruptcy) · h3:Counter-metrics=NSM ship least anti-metrics least counter-metric. · wf=**Confirm archetype.** Use Amplitude framework pick attention transaction productivity communication subscriber. **Draft candidate NSMs.** Score against five tests (Customer value Strategic alignment Leading Single number Movable). **Pick winner.** team commits one. Document decision rejected alternatives. **Decompose 3-5 input metrics.** Write explicit formula relating inputs NSM. **Assign 2-3 leading indicators input.** become daily dashboard. **Define anti-metrics counter-metrics.** least anti counter, explicit threshold. **Run `metric_tree_builder.py`.** Produce Mermaid tree team wiki JSON dashboard config. **Wire OKRs.** target moving one input metric. Objective NSM movement. **Re-review quarterly.** NSMs durable eternal; revisit strategy shifts. · h2:Tools=\| Tool \| Purpose \| Command \| · h2:Tools=\|------\|---------\|---------\| · h2:Tools=\| `metric_tree_builder.py` \| Build the NSM + inputs + leaders + anti/counter metric spec; render as Mermaid, JSON, or Markdown \| `python scripts/metric_tree_builder.py --input nsm_spec.json --format mermaid` \| · h2:Tools=\| `metric_tree_builder.py --demo` \| Inspect a worked example for a SaaS productivity NSM \| `python scripts/metric_tree_builder.py --demo --format markdown` \| · h2:Troubleshooting=\| Symptom \| Likely Cause \| Resolution \| · h2:Troubleshooting=\|---------\|--------------\|------------\| · h2:Troubleshooting=\| Team has 5+ "NSM candidates" and cannot pick \| Strategic disagreement, not metric ambiguity \| Resolve the strategy decision first; the NSM debate is a proxy for "what business are we in" \| · h2:Troubleshooting=\| NSM is going up but customers report dissatisfaction \| NSM is being gamed; anti-metrics missing or not enforced \| Add explicit anti-metrics with thresholds; review weekly alongside the NSM \| · h2:Troubleshooting=\| Input metrics do not actually multiply/sum to the NSM \| Inputs are loosely related, not mathematically derived \| Rewrite the explicit formula; replace inputs that do not fit the formula \| · h2:Troubleshooting=\| Leading indicators are the same as input metrics \| Team confused lagging vs leading \| A leading indicator must move BEFORE the input metric (in time); move upstream in the funnel \| · h2:Troubleshooting=\| OKRs do not connect to NSM movement \| OKRs set independently of the NSM \| Rewrite Key Results so each one moves a specific input metric; the Objective is the NSM \| · h2:Troubleshooting=\| NSM is "revenue" \| Revenue is the lagging financial outcome, not the value delivered \| Pick a metric closer to customer value (e.g., paid weekly active accounts); revenue follows \| · h2:Troubleshooting=\| NSM changes every quarter \| Team is not committing; or strategy is genuinely changing every quarter (deeper problem) \| Commit to the NSM for at least 4 quarters; if strategy genuinely shifts that fast, the NSM exercise is premature \| · h2:Success Criteria=team state NSM one sentence hedging, NSM passes tests (customer value, strategic, leading, single number, movable), Inputs explicit mathematical relationship NSM (formula documented), input 2-3 leading indicators move days/weeks before input, least anti-metrics counter-metric, explicit thresholds, OKR Key Result targets moving one input metric, NSM appears weekly status update quarterly review, new hire explain NSM one path move within their first month · h3:metric_tree_builder.py=Builds Mermaid tree NSM inputs leading indicators anti-metrics counter-metrics. outputs spec JSON formatted Markdown. · h3:metric_tree_builder.py=\| Flag \| Type \| Default \| Description \| · h3:metric_tree_builder.py=\|------\|------\|---------\|-------------\| · h3:metric_tree_builder.py=\| `--input` \| string \| (required unless `--demo`) \| Path to JSON NSM spec file \| · h3:metric_tree_builder.py=\| `--demo` \| flag \| false \| Use built-in SaaS productivity demo NSM \| · h3:metric_tree_builder.py=\| `--format` \| choice \| mermaid \| Output: json, markdown, mermaid, confluence, notion, linear \| · h3:metric_tree_builder.py=\| `--output` \| string \| stdout \| Output file path \| · h3:Input JSON shape=`{ \· "nsm": { \· "name": "Weekly active accounts that publish >=1 deliverable", \· "archetype": "productivity", \· "formula": "WAA * (publishers / WAA)",` · h3:Mermaid output sample=`graph TD \· NSM["NSM: Weekly active accounts publishing >=1 deliverable<br/>Target: 22000 by 2026-09-30"] \· NSM --> I1["Input: Weekly active accounts (WAA)"] \· NSM --> I2["Input: Publisher rate"] \· I1 --> L1a["Lead: Day-1 session count"]`